lts imply that broader socio-cultural factors discussed in the book are necessary: a country can only embark on positive developmental trends if all factors are present simultaneously, since cumulative effect and synergy are required.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2022) 0aTársadalmi változásokxKözep-Kelet-Európay1989-. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Eastern.2bisacsh  aEconomic conditions, Social conditions, Indicators, Sustainable development.1 aAdam, Frane, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMakarovic, Matej, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRončević, Borut, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aTomšič, Matevž, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCentral European University Press eBook-Package 2013-1998z978311078055040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789633863916423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789633863916/original  a978-3-11-078055-0  Central European University Press eBook-Package 2013-1998c1998d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK